\subtree{
\taxon{Subsection}
\title{Equivalence between the pullback powers of families and arrows}
\author{fredrikbakke}

\subtree[stt-00EP]{
\taxon{Theorem}
\title{The equivalence of unstraightened pullback powers}

\p{
Given #{f : A \to B} and #{g : (b : B) \to X(b) \to Y(b)}, the dependent pullback
power is equivalent, as an arrow, to the unstraightening of the fibrewise pullback
power.

##{\pulldpow_f g \simeq \pulldpow^{\mathrm f}_{\text{unstraight},f} g}
}

\proof{
\p{
First, consider the codomain of #{\pulldpow_f g}, #{\Hom^{\mathrm d}(f,g)}. It
consists of a section #{i : \Pi_{(b : B)} Y(b)} together with a section
#{j : \Pi_{(a : A)} X(f(a))} such that #{i \circ f \sim g \circ j}. Reindexing the
second piece fibrewise over the fibres of #{f} this data is equivalent to the type

##{
\Sigma_{(i : \Pi_{(b : B)} Y(b))}
\Pi_{(b : B)} (\fibre{f}{b} \to \fibre{g(b)}{i(b)}),
}

so the codomain of #{\pulldpow_f g} is identified with the base of the fibrewise
pullback power family.
}

\p{
Second, consider the fibrewise pullback power family over this base: over a section
#{i : \Pi_{(b : B)} Y(b)} its fibre is the type

##{
\Pi_{(b : B)} (\fibre{f}{b} \to \fibre{g(b)}{i(b)}).
}

Unstraightening this family essentially adds, for each #{b : B}, a null-homotopy of
the map #{\fibre{f}{b} \to \fibre{g(b)}{i(b)}}. After exchanging the outer
#{\Sigma}-types and #{\Pi}-types, the domain becomes

##{
\Pi_{(b : B)}
\Sigma_{(y : Y(b))}
\Sigma_{(k : \fibre{f}{b} \to \fibre{g(b)}{y})}
\nullhtpy(k).
}

For each #{b : B} this is the [pointed-total presentation](stt-00F5) of the map
#{g(b) : X(b) \to Y(b)} at #{\fibre{f}{b}}, and hence it is equivalent
to #{X(b)}. Taking the dependent product over #{B} this gives an equivalence between
the domain of the unstraightened fibrewise pullback power and #{\Pi_{(b : B)} X(b)}.
}

\p{
Under these identifications, a section #{\ell : \Pi_{(b : B)} X(b)} is sent to the
family whose fibre over #{b} is the point #{g(b)(\ell(b)) : Y(b)} together with the
constant map
#{\fibre{f}{b} \to \fibre{g(b)}{g(b)(\ell(b))}}, sending every point of
#{\fibre{f}{b}} to #{(\ell(b), \refl)} and its evident null-homotopy. This is
exactly the image of #{\ell} under the unstraightened fibrewise pullback power.
Thus the domain and codomain identifications are compatible with the two arrows, so
they assemble into an equivalence of arrows. Passing to fibres over corresponding
codomain points then yields the equivalence of the associated fibre families. \qed
}
}

%```agda
\agda{
module _
  {ً‌“¤1 ً‌“¤2 ً‌“¤3 ً‌“¤4}
